<subSubSection id="C34B65341630F70AFF2BFEFBFDB3F9A7" pageId="4" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEE36BF1630F70AFF2BFEFBFDB3F9A7" blockId="4.[166,1225,175,746]" pageId="4" pageNumber="17">
Diagnosis. 
<emphasis id="B925EAAD1630F70AFE8DFEFBFE6DFA04" bold="true" box="[381,477,303,329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="17">Female:</emphasis>
Head (
<figureCitation id="136A2A3A1630F70AFDC8FEFBFDC8FA07" box="[568,632,303,330]" captionStart="Figs 6–11" captionStartId="3.[174,213,1800,1822]" captionTargetBox="[228,1176,577,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-141@3.[212,1195,560,1776]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 6–11. Females of Cheilosia psilophthalma (figs 6–8, 10) and C. urbana (figs 9, 11): 6 — habitus, dorsal view; 7 — habitus, lateral view; 8, 9 — head, frontal view; 10, 11 — claws of fore leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404162/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="17">fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Face black with facial tubercle and lower facial margin well developed (
<figureCitation id="136A2A3A1630F70AFE4CFE9BFE48FA27" box="[444,504,335,362]" captionStart="Figs 6–11" captionStartId="3.[174,213,1800,1822]" captionTargetBox="[228,1176,577,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-141@3.[212,1195,560,1776]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 6–11. Females of Cheilosia psilophthalma (figs 6–8, 10) and C. urbana (figs 9, 11): 6 — habitus, dorsal view; 7 — habitus, lateral view; 8, 9 — head, frontal view; 10, 11 — claws of fore leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404162/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="17">fig. 7</figureCitation>
); lateral parts of frons densely covering with whitish pile, dust spots not connected to dusting on face (
<figureCitation id="136A2A3A1630F70AFD71FEBBFD0EFAC7" box="[641,702,367,394]" captionStart="Figs 6–11" captionStartId="3.[174,213,1800,1822]" captionTargetBox="[228,1176,577,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-141@3.[212,1195,560,1776]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 6–11. Females of Cheilosia psilophthalma (figs 6–8, 10) and C. urbana (figs 9, 11): 6 — habitus, dorsal view; 7 — habitus, lateral view; 8, 9 — head, frontal view; 10, 11 — claws of fore leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404162/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="17">fig. 8</figureCitation>
); basoflagellomere reddish, 1.5 times longer than wide, arista nearly bare; eyes entirely covered with short whitish pile (
<figureCitation id="136A2A3A1630F70AFBD0FE5BFBEEFAE7" box="[1056,1118,399,426]" captionStart="Figs 6–11" captionStartId="3.[174,213,1800,1822]" captionTargetBox="[228,1176,577,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-141@3.[212,1195,560,1776]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 6–11. Females of Cheilosia psilophthalma (figs 6–8, 10) and C. urbana (figs 9, 11): 6 — habitus, dorsal view; 7 — habitus, lateral view; 8, 9 — head, frontal view; 10, 11 — claws of fore leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404162/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="17">fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Thorax with short pale pile, black bristles on hind rim of scutellum present; upper and lower parts of hairs on katepisternum widely separated. Legs: femora black with small apical part pale, tibiae pale with narrow incomplete black rings below middle (
<figureCitation id="136A2A3A1630F70AFC70FE3BFC0DF947" box="[896,957,495,522]" captionStart="Figs 6–11" captionStartId="3.[174,213,1800,1822]" captionTargetBox="[228,1176,577,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-141@3.[212,1195,560,1776]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 6–11. Females of Cheilosia psilophthalma (figs 6–8, 10) and C. urbana (figs 9, 11): 6 — habitus, dorsal view; 7 — habitus, lateral view; 8, 9 — head, frontal view; 10, 11 — claws of fore leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404162/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="17">fig. 7</figureCitation>
); tarsomeres 2–3 of all legs pale, 4–5 blackish, first tarsomeres of fore legs pale with dark patch on upper side, ones of mid legs pale; all claws black (
<figureCitation id="136A2A3A1630F70AFDE5FDFBFDD0F907" box="[533,608,559,586]" captionStart="Figs 6–11" captionStartId="3.[174,213,1800,1822]" captionTargetBox="[228,1176,577,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-141@3.[212,1195,560,1776]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 6–11. Females of Cheilosia psilophthalma (figs 6–8, 10) and C. urbana (figs 9, 11): 6 — habitus, dorsal view; 7 — habitus, lateral view; 8, 9 — head, frontal view; 10, 11 — claws of fore leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404162/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="17">fig. 10</figureCitation>
